  "prompt": "Has anyone been arrested for downloading torrent in India?",
  "response": "While torrenting itself is not illegal, downloading copyrighted content without permission is against the law in India. There have been instances of legal action against individuals for downloading copyrighted material:\n\n1. Some cases have been reported where:\n- Internet Service Providers (ISPs) have been asked to block torrent sites\n- Copyright holders have sent legal notices\n- Occasional arrests have occurred, particularly for large-scale piracy\n\n2. Potential consequences:\n- Legal notices\n- Fines\n- Potential criminal charges\n- Internet service disruption\n\n3. Risks vary based on:\n- Volume of downloaded content\n- Type of copyrighted material\n- Specific jurisdiction\n- Enforcement priorities\n\n4. Recommendations:\n- Use legal streaming platforms\n- Purchase content from authorized sources\n- Use VPN if downloading\n- Be aware of potential legal risks\n\nWhile widespread arrests are not common, legal risks do exist. The situation can change, so it's advisable to stay informed about current laws and enforcement practices.",
